In addition to the duties set forth elsewhere in this subtitle, in this Part II of this subtitle, the Commission shall:
Act as the State agency to represent the State under Title VI of the federal Public Health Service Act; and
Periodically participate in or perform analyses and studies that relate to:
Adequacy of services and financial resources to meet the needs of the population;
Distribution of health care resources;
Allocation of health care resources;
Costs of health care in relationship to available financial resources; or
Any other appropriate matter.
